ZCZC EE57
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 102300 UTC
MONDAY EVENING AN AREA OF LOW PRESSURE 997 WILL BE SITUATED IN NERN CULLERCOATS
GRADUALLY MOV N-EWARDS TO BECOME LOCATED OVER SCANDINAVIA BY TUESDAY SLWY
FLN IN THE PROCESS. MEANWHILE ANOTHER AREA OF LOW PRESSURE 997 WILL BE SITUATED
OVER THE ATLANTIC AND WILL MOV SE TO BECOME LOCATED OVER FITZROY ON TUESDAY
SLWY FLN. AT THE SAME TIME AN AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE 1021 CENTRED OVER THE
MID-ATLANTIC WILL BEGIN TO EXTEND EWARDS ACROSS UK SEA AREAS FM TUESDAY ONWARDS
WITH LOW PRESSURE REMAINING SITUATED OVER SCANDINAVIA DURING THE REMAINDER
OF THE PERIOD. OCNL STRG WINDS ACROSS FITZROY SOLE AND SHANNON DURING MONDAY
EVENING AND THROUGHOUT TUESDAY EXTENDING INTO LUNDY AND FASTNET FOR A TIME
ON TUESDAY. STRG WINDS WILL GRADUALLY EASE ACROSS ALL NITON SEA AREAS DURING
WEDNESDAY. NO FURTHER HAZARDOUS WINDS ARE EXP ACROSS NITON ON THURSDAY
